reviews.text: Fantastic statue right in front of monas , must see, however not easy to get great picture, but with effort can

What can i say about this place? It's majestic and artistic, the place itself is on the center of protocol Street. It's quite okay for walk here but not sure if it's a great place to take a picture without everyone staring at you. Maybe if you got a good camera, i recommend you to take a picture at night, even tho the area would be so full and loud with traffic activity around.
Just aware of the statue's name after so long ... It is a monumental architecture ...
grand sculpture of Arjuna hero god riding his chariot with horses striding forward the fountain at Thamrin rounabout , off merdeka park(Monas) . one of photo check in point in Jakarta..
Wonderful sunday, cloudy hey...can breath till drop..

Nice place  to escape the Jakarta traffic at sunset; peaceful and pleasant.  Locals seem to like it too.  Pretty open area, so it doesn't feel crowded.  Would recommend going before checking out the food options nearby.

It's a good place to visit: the gallery of mini dioramas on the ground floor is quite interesting, unfortunately it leaves more questions about the history of Indonesia than explains (I mean, if Indonesian rebellions against Dutch were always so successful then how the whole territory was kept for 300 years by invaders?). 
The view from the top is very good, but long wait to get to an elevator and the framing on top hinders the view quite a lot.
Anyway, I'd say the museum is must see.

Recommended stop in Jakarta. Very touristy, but not too expensive like some tourist traps. 
I recommend using the shuttle from the gate to the monument. Otherwise, its about a 10 minute walk with very little shade.
At the monument, expect to have an hour wait to go up top. Longer during busy times.

Beautiful and a must see if in Jakarta. Lacks in the actual museeum part as there are no places to sit for the entire visit. Also the top floor with the view only opens in the late afternoon for some reason.

Great place to see the view of the city when you go to the top. The ticket place is no where near the monument, but the bus pick up area in the opposite site of the monument which is not far. You go from the underground floor to reach into the monument area. The price is not that expensive, so worth to try. Underground, there are displays of Indonesia history, when you go up by the elevator, you can see the view. It close at 5 or 6 pm, so if you want to go to the  top, you should come earlier to buy the ticket, there are many people esp, holiday or weekend.

One of the most remarkable open space in Jakarta. The space itself releases positive energy. Making people want to move and do fun activities or stay still laying down on the grass and some seating area around. Jogging track, futsal field, amphitheatre, any many space for activities are available. Dancing fountain is played 3 times a day 18.30, 19.30, 20.30. With lights play with Indonesian national and folk song that beautifully arranged for the fountain show. Trees are all around the place, take shelter under its shades would be really nice. There are not many street vendor, just some in the evening near Hotel Borobudur near motorcycle park. Toilets are clean and nice. This park is built with a sense of modern style but somehow still feels nostalgic. Some of the facility was unkept, like the swing near wooden house. At night, the lamps give a romantic touch to the park. A place that bring comfort at the center of Jakarta

It was a great place to spend your afternoon. You can  jog, play basketball, football, take picture or just stroll around. There will be water fountain show at 6.30 pm and 7.30 pm. This show lasts about 15-20 minutes.

Nice place to hangout on saturday night with family, friend or lover. Here you can watch the dancing fountain. It's free. One of the historical place in Jakarta. Also you can taking a good photos here. There's 3 session of the dancing fountain show. Every show, it's only 15 minutes. So don't miss it! I came here on the 3rd session, on 19.15.
Beautiful park in the middle of the city. An attraction marked a historical symbol. Worth visit to spend time exercising here, or just hanging around and have a picnic with friends.
It's one of the newest open public areas in Jakarta where it has a wide pedestrian walk surrounded by shady trees and it has ampitheater with fountain. A perfect place to jog & workout your cardio.

Nice place  to escape the Jakarta traffic at sunset; peaceful and pleasant.  Locals seem to like it too.  Pretty open area, so it doesn't feel crowded.  Would recommend going before checking out the food options nearby.

The view from the top is very good, but long wait to get to an elevator and the framing on top hinders the view quite a lot.
Anyway, I'd say the museum is must see.

I recommend using the shuttle from the gate to the monument. Otherwise, its about a 10 minute walk with very little shade.
At the monument, expect to have an hour wait to go up top. Longer during busy times.

Beautiful and a must see if in Jakarta. Lacks in the actual museeum part as there are no places to sit for the entire visit. Also the top floor with the view only opens in the late afternoon for some reason.

Great place to see the view of the city when you go to the top. The ticket place is no where near the monument, but the bus pick up area in the opposite site of the monument which is not far. You go from the underground floor to reach into the monument area. The price is not that expensive, so worth to try. Underground, there are displays of Indonesia history, when you go up by the elevator, you can see the view. It close at 5 or 6 pm, so if you want to go to the  top, you should come earlier to buy the ticket, there are many people esp, holiday or weekend.

Very small museum, cool knowledgeable guides that seem to master a lot of the countrie's historic, traditional and mythological stories. In an hour you can see most part of it. There is a little shop outside of the museum where you can buy some artifacts that are also available elsewhere at lesser price.
I like this place but I would love it if it had enough traditional and local object. I think it doesn't represent enough the national heritage

I loved visiting this museum. I wish I could've taken pictures. Nevertheless, our tour guide, William Dayo, was very well versed in each of the exhibits. It was really nice to have someone with us who gave us in depth information on what we were viewing. It gave us a deeper understanding and appreciation for each of the artifacts.
It was nice. The museum has a lot to offer in cultural history and I was happy to see them opened on a Sunday.

This museum continues the tradition of equating Western African culture and history mainly with masks (sarcasm). It could almost be interchangeable with the museum's in Dakar and Bamako except they both have a second floor dedicated to textiles. 

Granted, the masks are interesting and high quality, but they are completely decontextualized with cryptic captions an little explanation tying anything together.

There is one table showing the evolution of money that was nice. 

It's one of the few times I wished there was a museum gift shop with some books. 

Weirdly they don't allow photography either, as if history should be hidden. 

Avoid the restaurant out back it is way overpriced and there are better maquis around.

A very good place for those who like color and green plants. 
Wide and open place for children and your family. 
Quite place for relaxation time. 
If you want to walk, this place very good for you.

Quiet place. 
Charged us 25 EGP/person .
it’s alongside the beach but with minimal spots having direct sea view.
No entrance to the palace but you can walk around and take photos

A v.good place for those who like the green color.
Wide and open place for your family and children.
You can enjoy walking alongside the beach without swimming.
A magnificent place. It should be considered part of the world heritage
Marvelous gardens and open areas for children and outdoor activities ... Ticket is 25 LE per person or car.

A great place to visit either alone or with people. The museum has been renovated so it has modern aesthetics and fitted with modern gadget to help learning about the Indonesian independence proclamation more interactive .

Home of Maeda Tadashi, or people known him well as Laksamana Maeda. A Japanese Navy officer that reside at this building during Japanese occupation in Batavia 1942-1945. Proclamation statement of Independence formulated here by Indonesian founding fathers in mid August 1945

If you want to know about the history of the Proclamation of the Republic of Indonesia, you have definitely visit this museum! You can get the information from the museum's guide about the history of proclamation. From the World War II until the proclamation. The staff are very friendly and there is a car park too. If you want to pray there are also a mosque for the muslim and church for the christian near this building. You can do a prayer at the Sunda Kelapa mosque for the muslim. It is about 150 meters from the museum. The entrance ticket is just 1000 IDR for group and 2000 IDR for individual.

Very well preserved; abundance information, very good condition and enjoyable experience.

Price is too cheap :)
I really this to be expensive, bit higher if not, so that people understand and appreciate how valuable this historical place.

Enjoy it to the max.
Lots of insights.
Great place to lewrn about proklamasi. The place was comfort and quite enough.

This mosque is the 3rd largest in the world. Didn’t get the chance to go inside. But was absolutely beautiful from the sky up. The mosque is a walks worth from the national monument in central Jakarta. There was also a beautiful cathedral right near it as well.

This place is very great even for tourists. There are helpful guides who will give you advice about checking in. They provide free robes to cover up and you can explore and see several large areas of the mosque. It is very beautiful and big. Feel free to give donations, but everything is free.

Mesjid Istiqlal is a famous mosque in Jakarta. The mosque is so huge that it can accommodate as many as 120,000 people making it the biggest mosque in South East Asia. The mosque is an architectural delight, and resonates peace when one goes inside. It serves as the praying place for the muslims of the country but it is visited by everyone from all walks of life.

It's the largest mosque in South East Asia and in Jakarta..
No entry fees for this.
It's location is very prime in central Jakarta and is very close to Monas and Merdeka Square.
Just opposite to it is the Jakarta Cathedral..
It's huge in size.. They have big parking facility available but it's crowded most of the time specially in on weekends so keep that in mind.
Carry a polythene along to keep your footwears in it else there would be people just outside selling it to them.
There is a counter where u can deposit your shoes if you are a local and Muslim. In case your are a tourist from other country, then just right to the counter is an information desk sort where u can enter your details in the register.. Also, you will be required to put your shoes in the guest room and not the usual place.
If you are not Muslim, then you will not be allowed to go to first floor of the mosque. You can go on the second floor and click photographs.
Make sure you are well dressed and covered when u arrive here (both men and women) else they provide clothes to cover you up.
The architecture is world class and good place for praying.. 
Overall nice place and worth visiting once

Indonesia's largest mosque. Non-moslems are welcome to visit and take photos, as long as they submit to the basic rules such as keeping quiet and not littering. Take off your shoes and store it for free inside; all kinds of footwears are not allowed inside all mosques in the world.
Good taste but the sausage a little bit small.
One of the rare places to get a decent hotdog in Jakarta because hotdogs aren't popular here. Prices range between IDR 20,000-40,000.

Di Google Maps tulisnya tutup jam 
10 malam
Saya 3 jam yang lalu ke sini dari atrium Senen, sampe sini masih belum jam 10 malam, masih kurang lebih jam setengah 10 malam, Sarinah masih rame, tapi yang saya liat Hotdog Booth udah tutup
Saya nanya sama mas-mas yang kebetulan lagi di deket situ, katanya ini Hotdog Booth baru tutup
Pas saya nanya itu masih kurang lebih jam 9 lewat 45 menit, belum jam 10
Saya pengen cari hotdog, susah nyarinya
Seingat saya, hotdog ini asalnya dari barat, sama kayak burger
Di atrium Senen tadi saya cari makanan ini di 3 restoran Amerika, yang pertama A&W, yang kedua Burger King, yang ketiga KFC, tiga-tiganya jual burger. Saya pikir, kalo mereka jual burger, mungkin mereka jual hotdog, ternyata kebalikan dari apa yang saya pikirkan, mereka ketiga-tiganya gak jual hotdog sama sekali
Karna gak dapet, saya cari di Waze, tempat jual hotdog paling deket dari sini (atrium Senen di mana), saya cek setiap tempat di Google Maps, kalo ada ulasannya, saya ke situ, kalo gak ada ulasan, saya abaikan, ketemulah tempat ini, Hotdog Booth, saya liat di Google Maps ditulis tutupnya jam 10 malem, saya pikir keburu, bener aja sampe sini belom jam 10 malem, masih sekitar jam setengah 10 malem, malah tutup
Lumayan bisa buat ngisi perut sambil nunggu travel berangkat. Ramah.

I went for lunch. Nice menu selection and plenty of seating. They have two separate areas for room for non-smoking and another room smoker's. My meal was very good and was served in a reasonable time. Prices were also very reasonable.  Flavors were good. Plenty of parking .

The restaurant have many various menus and the taste is good. The ice cream is good too. The price is quite okay for a cafe. Sometimes they have live music indoor. This place is good for chit chat. The parking lot is not big, but you can park the car outside.
Warm and friendly ambience, live music, various menu, I just can't handle the smoke. Wrong choice for a passive smoker.
Pasta and pizza were quite decent... Vanilla gelato was really good! Very rich and sweet! Overall a good dining experience...
I had a great night here with the Sunday night ACapella group, they’re very good and a lot of fun, well worth seeing and something different to your usual bands.  The pizzas are good too.

A place to reminisce. It has a sense of nostalgia even if you're not even around that era. This place serves one of the best classic ice creams in Jakarta.

Orders are very quick to be taken and served, so you don't have to worry about waiting. In busy hours you will be having trouble looking for a chair to sit, since it's too crowded!

The ice creams are really great, aesthetics aside. It has an affordable price range for people to hang around friends and family while eating ice cream!

Old ice cream joint. But the ice cream taste is unforgettable, loved by all ages. Their specialty is the nougat ice cream, light green colored, with the crushed nuts as the topping. No air con, some people who can't stand the heat, would rather eat the ice cream in their own car in the parking lot.

Tasted nostalgic, however not my really my fave compared to modern ice cream. The place is humid and crowded, gotta move fast if you want to have a seat. Despite all that, I still coming here whenever I have guests from outside Jakarta. It's definitely a must visit place if you love history or if you want to see and feel the "old Jakarta". I plan to visit here again to taste their orange float.

Here comes the legendary Italian ice cream in Central Jakarta! I ordered a spaghetti ice cream by Goj*k. It was neatly packed in styrofoam. In addition, the ice cream was still perfectly frozen when it arrived. Thanks to the power of dry ice 😂. Basically this ice cream tastes so light and natural since it is very milky, not creamy. Moreover, the sweetness is also proportional. Yummy!

This old landmark use to be the no 1 destination for ice cream lover in Jakarta. The business is kinda slow nowadays. The taste of the ice cream itself is kinda declining. Still good as a hangout place for those who want to have nostalgic memory.

My second time having a lunch here. This is a legendary Chinese noodle shop in Jakarta. The room here are huge, with comfortable spaces between the tables. They also served a lot of different Chinese foods other than noodle.

The amount of foods served here are ridiculously huge that you can share it with 1 or 2 persons. If you want to eat by your own, try to order the 'Mini' (smaller) serving for your food. Every food in here tastes okay to pretty good. Will come back for more in the future.

Suitable for family. Also safe for Moslem (Halal-certified).
The noodles from childhood memory where my mother used to bring me and my sister. Taste still ok. Just there's no pepper in the small bottle. Place a bit old. Still nice for an eating place.

Good food but little dishes. 
I was wondered for the little dishes.
If you are too hungry it is not the place for having lunch or dinner.
The bathroom is really dirty but the workers are nice and speedy.
But l told you....the food portions are too little for my stomach.

Good taste of halal middle, located at gang kelinci.
Venue is fairly clean with very small parking area.
However the taste of bakmi is mouthwatering.

Legendary Noodle, I always thought that Bakmi Grand Kelinci at mall are their branchs, but i was wrong. Maybe there is time when these branches is part of original Bakmi Gang Kelinci, but now is no more. The taste difference is really huge in my opinion. I am not here for decades, tasting Bakmi Grand Kelinci at mall make me losing interest, because I thought the standard become lower. But I give it a try when I am at Pasar Baru to visit the original store, and i was suprised, it still great! It  certainly bring back my childhood memory. Already visit here a couple time since then. Recommend it with all my heart but do not expect a very clean or great service, this is still a traditional noodle stall with AC with great taste noodle. (PS this is halal food and their fried noodle is also superb).
Great food and amazing atmosphere! Amazing place to take tourists or guests, they will love the fishpond that surrounds the restaurant.
Old resto but their quality always good and taste same as usual. It would be nice if they put an AC for the resto. Divided the smoking area properly
Lots of delicious mouth watering food here! Better make reservations before you come here, if not..either you will wait too long or you will go home empty handed

One of the earliest restaurant in late 1990s that serves authentic Indonesian cuisines. I visited this place sometime in 1999 when it was first opened and my latest visit brought back the good taste memories of yesteryear.

Their specialty is gurame fish and it can be prepared in many varieties, like deep fried, assam pedas, soup and many others. You can refer to their menu.

I ordered the deep fried version and the meat was tender and we can even chew on the crispy bones! They also serve chicken, vegetables and bean cakes. Their stuff toufu is good.

Their sambal is also very nice but can be spicy to those who are not accustomed to it. I enjoyed the food thoroughly.
The best "gurame goreng kipas" in town. The restaurant is quite full, so better make a reservation.

A chain restaurant serving good Indonesian food.
Had the satay, a tofu salad, mixed fried appetizers. Food was very good. Place was very clean and stylish. Seemed very popular with the locals.

This is an excellent restaurant. It's not too crowded, even though it's located in an lively area. I didn't have much luck with food in other places, mostly the food was dry and spicy. But I enjoyed the sate and gado-gado. The wait staff was friendly and efficient. They kept the place spotlessly clean.
The Menteng one of the best Sate Khas Senayan outlets. Huge outdoor area for smokers and similarly huge air conditioned indoors area.

The service was awful. We ordered for 5 people and came as 6 orders, which we easily waived, but some of the orders arrived really late and it was stone cold as if the food have been sitting in a fridge for a long time (even the plate was cold). The service was all over the place and even though I understand that we came during lunch hours, but the kitchen staff were not prepared for it, and we unfortunately paid the price.
*update*
Against my better judgement, came there the second time, and just like I predicted, the quality haven't improved since. Some of the order arrived really late, and the quality is just sub par. The staffs are clearly not handled for lunch hour rush, it generate this curiosity about the system that they're running behind the counter. Also it'll be better for them to provide some sort of feedback form or if they already have one put it in each table. The customers aren't happy and they should take notice of that.
My final final verdict: don't go to this place for lunch.

Love to have lunch or dinner in this location. Clean and have good ambience with fast response and nice service. Still reasonable for the pricing consider to the quality of their services and the food/taste. They accept cash and card payments.
Ok
wow

Ayam bakar wong solo ini tmpat.y d dlam ITC.y yah atau g mna ? 
Soal.y udah dri kmrin* d cari 😅
Hmm bagi anda yg blom nyobain makan dimari, anda dpt mencoba menu favorite restaurant yaitu nasi dgn ayam bakar. Manteb2

yg bikin nagih sambel nya mantul, 
harga sesuai lah sama rasa.
A New Way of living faith, sharing love and being hape...
Misa Jumper

I visited them once, and I tasted beef ribs and beef steak. The restaurant building is just mind blowing. It's very nice and clean. Stuffs are well mannered. If I want to talk about the tastes of the beef ribs and beef steak then it wasn't so exciting. I think it was average in my opinion. But the place is just stunning.

VERY BAD SERVICE. I asked if my hot tea is refillable. He made sure i ordered hot tea and not iced tea. Then i replied, are you saying i lie just to get a free refill? (my glass is still warm and he should feel it too. Then he gave me this (look at the photo). Great job Tony Roma's.  You refill my tea with hot water..
mouthwatering babyback ribs! been here first long time a go with my family but the taste never change. pricey but the food came in a big portion, you can share them.

This place looks tired, the wooden frames falling. We sat in one corner with artifical trees that dropped some dirts to our table. It's sad to see such condition considering the food prices are so high. The ribs quite dry and my steak was rare instead of medium.

You know exactly what it will be like before you get there, and yet you decide to go anyway. Surrounded by large family parties with screaming children and grown ups in pajamas, TR delivers precisely the kind of generic eating experience you know it will, with added added chaos. The servers were prompt and friendly, however the hostess who “welcomed” me set the tone by ignoring me while chatting with another group and then welcoming another party that shoved me out of the way, despite making eye contact with me earlier. The food is mediocre, the coleslaw bland and the sad baked potato with but a hint of sour cream and a tiny sprinkle of rubbery cold cheese that accompanied my chewy (!) ribs were filling yet far from satisfying. I could not recommend this place less however, I know that you, just as I did, will ignore your mind screaming no when your heart is so emphatically set on ribs, and suddenly Tony Roma’s seems like a great idea because how bad could it really be? It’s the kind of experience you’ll manage to forget in 10 years when your heart twangs and the irresistible urge draws you back to Tony Roma’s. Good thing it’s only an experience you have to endure once in a decade.
The best Japanese restaurant I have tasted! The food is amazing and taste authentic. The place is comfortable and homey. Definitely will go there every time I have the opportunity

Great Japanese home-cooked-style food.
Ordered Kiku set, flavor & portion was very delicious and comforting. Value for money is great. Warm ambience. Definitely will return again. Highly recommended.
Nice place to eat authentic Japanese food. I tried the Ogura ice cream, and it was so delicious!

Really love this place!!
They’re only play the japanese instrumental song through their speaker in medium level. the atmosphere make you talk in low voice ;)
Nice place, traditional, feel calm! Nice food especially Ume Set!

Feels like you have dine in a fancy garden. This outlet offer great taste of foods and beverages. If you wanna having lunch meeting or even private meeting, Penang Bistro Menteng will accommodate you well. 

Try my favourite Tom Yum Soup, Salted Egg Mushroom, Apple Crumble Pie with a glass of Ice Thai Tea.

Worth the price.

Scale 0-5

Location : 4
Place & Ambience : 4
Variety of Menu : 4
Taste : 4
Price : 3.8
Love the place. Very well designed. Have private rooms for small events or medium events. Food is great, a bit pricey but still worth it.
Great food. Nice taste.... a memorable food as it was long time ago since i visited this place and it give me the same memory when i came back. Nice management, I believe. Nice roti canai :)
one of the best chinese/indonesian food you can get in jakarta region. all the food are amazing esoecially the shrimps and octopus!

Very cozy restaurant, the dishes here are so yummy and drink here also nice, i have tried leci sereh .. it is very refreshing, the service also great here, they really make sure you are comfy while having your lunch. Suitable for meetings for groups or even for hangout with fellas. But the traffic outside sometimes what make us consider to have a lunch here, but overall i love the ambience.
Superb place to worship and pray in Buddhist-Mahayana Tradition. Friendly people inside. Come and Ehipassiko :)
Nice center
Nice place. Good place. Good ambiance.
Nice
Buddhist temple
Great food, great staff, and lovely intimate atmosphere.

delicious breakfast 
nice atmosphere
Well cooked, interesting food in pleasant surroundings.

Artistic and unique interior design. From outside it’s just like a common restaurant but inside will be different ambience. About the taste was not too special but you can have it while enjoying the situation. Too pity we can’t find praying room at this restaurant so for you who want to do then you will need to do in small place near the warehouse for the beverages/wines ( sounds not really intended for a praying room). In overall, while enjoying the lunch or dinner, you also can listen to the Javanese music (gamelan) which can make a difference feeling- peaceful and relax. It’s quite nice.

I love this place.
Ambience is just.. unique, 1 or 2 rooms feels creepy but overall is ok, a bit dark yes but feel cozy.
Food is of course great, mostly the food tastes rich from coconut milk, and the sweet banana is lovely. They also make marvelous cocktail.
Price is average to high, about $20-25/person.

Service is great, I told the server brought a friend from USA and they took us for a mini tour around the resto completed with the history and explanation about each room’s theme, especially the “Lara Djonggrang” room
Stunning menu and delicious food. Menu is vast so expect to spend a few minutes (hours) taking a look through. Service is also very good.

The best food in the neighborhood/city. I'm sure there are other places but the food here made its way to the list. Ingredients combined together in a vibrant chorus. First glance suggests most of the items on the menu were fairly priced. I recommend trying this place if you have the time.
Restaurant is very cozy and unique. Menu is familiar with Indonesia people. Very recommend to have lunch or dinner in this restaurant.

They doing baby ear piercing here. The staff that work at the jewellery store are really friendly. They ways gave two staff to pierce baby ears as they do both at the same time to prevent added stress to the child which is perfect

Ignite Records is the best record store in the city. A real vinyl cavern that is packed with fairly priced records to suit a wide range of tastes. Rich (the owner) is a real gent, very knowledgeable and accommodating. The store is friendly and welcoming. Important we keep this indie going!
Legendary Birmingham fixture! Great place to get alternative/rock clothing and accessories  in an iconic location in the centre of town for nearly 50 years.

I have been going to Oasis for over 10 years now and every time you go in it is exciting, literally like a kid in a sweet shop. There is always something new and exciting going on. Highly recommend it!

Oasis has lost it appeal and is no longer a fashion markets. It's now full of rude and over priced tattoo parlours and pretentious "clothing shops". Not to mention the shops selling drug paraphernalia. 

Both inside and out the markets are rundown and are stuck in the 1980s and is in need of updating and bring in to this millennium. 
The markets also attracts the wrong kind of people and is a center of anti-social behaviour. I have often seen the police and security patrolling and moving people on. 

The Oasis markets are full of empty stalls and shops, which adds to the rundown feeling.

In conclusion, I would not recommend visting the markets for this reason.

It's a Nicholson's pub, quite easy to miss (you need to duck under an archway with a doorway somewhat hidden to the side that drops you down a staircase to a cellar dwelling.

Met up with some family friends for dinner who recommended this place; we were shown to a table deep inside the premises and decided to opt for pies. The meal was good, beer fine (a mixture of Nicholson's own and some other guest beers) and service excellent.  I decided to try a pudding, cheesecake with a generous dollop of cream.

The total bill for 4 people for meals plus plenty of beers came to under £100 - excellent value for what we had. Will definitely return if I'm in the area.
Wonderful place. Fabulous premises, great food and brilliant staff. Couldn't have been better and cannot wait to go there again.

Lovely little hideaway with a great atmosphere and eclectic clientele. A good range of reasonably priced wines and ales to suit any taste. Bar staff are polite and helpful. Wheelchair access through a lift

Always a fun place to dine out. Standard pub F&B. Great atmosphere on Friday night. Very busy. Unusual decor too. Reservations recommended. Private parties can take over a larger than usual space so you've been warned! ;-). Good service and happy waiting staff. Thank you. See you again.

An unusual themed bar with so much potential. Great gin selection but if it isn't on the menu,, they can't do cocktails. Interesting Roman meets Egyptian theme but in need of a clean. Thick dust on the light shade over our table, cobwebs on the curtains. A real shame as it could be a great location.

Great vibe great food good place to hang out but for me the place a bit dark especially when you carry out children. I order bread pudding and it is delicious some of my friend order ice cream and banana split and also have a good response. Definitely will be back
Dessert was nice, pasta ok, ambience just so so.
GB bistro is used to be called Gelato Bar. The good thing about this place is they have smoking room inside with air conditioning. Mostly smoking area in senayan city are located outdoor.

This place was busy and popular back to years ago. It owner told me that years ago if you want to eat at this restaurant must booked a month before. 
It is a nice and good old restaurant. Food are nice. 
First time for me to visit this place. But I like it. Nice clean and classic place.
I can smell the old wood and peace feeling.
Love it.
Good taste and great place. its a nice chinesse restaurant in jakarta. i will come back again
Only visited as part of walking tour but a super ambience inside ...lovely one can of course visit there if in kota area however not advertised well
Although I did not have the chance to eat in this restaurant this time, taking a picture here will always remind me to come back here sometime in the future.
Nice food n nice place
Beautiful, clean harbour.
Top

The best and biggest harbour in Indonesia.

Take passengers not only from Jakarta but also from around West Java, because not available yet passengers harbour in this region for this time.

Of course, this place is very busy harbour for 24 hours, to take passengers to go anothers area or islands around Indonesia.
Huge harbour but muaceettt, specially Friday
love it!

Another place to escape from Jakarta.
It is not far from toll road, to access it is not a wasting time.
This place is good for kids to learn about mangrove forest ecosystem.
This sea side conservation  is suitable for nature lover to explore.
This great place is good to relax and walks for families.
It is a mangrove forest park in North Jakarta by the sea.
In this area there are restaurants, canteens, guest house or cottage, bamboo track above the water and boat tour.
This recreation place is home to some wild animals such as crabs, small fish, monitor lizards, monkeys, snakes and birds.
Best time is morning and afternoon to avoid the heat.
Mosquito repellent is recommended to avoid being bitten.
Things that make me sad is the garbage that litter the good scenery.
At the entrance gate aside from ticket, professional camera and even pocket camera are subjected to fee, plus food and drink are not allowed. Phone camera only is free of charge.
Overall this place is great.

This mangrove forest good for take a picture, it's natural view with the trees, the air, the estuary. The paths made of bamboo, surround the forest. Better you use flip flops to make it easier for you to walk on bamboo. I think it is necessary to use mosquito repellent there. The air there feels stuffy. The ticket on weekend is 30k per person and 10k for car. If you bring SLR camera you have to pay 300k. Pocket camera 150k and for prewedding photo shoot 1.5M

A wildlife sanctuary on the edges of busy city Jakarta. The mangrove forest is very interesting, plus they make it as traveling destination so the place also has facilities like restaurant, pray area, toilet, even guesthouses. The bridges that bring you entrance the forest deeper that you think is the most valuable thing for this place. Good for your children to know more about mangrove forest. Just one issue, the toilet is dirty, but this is forest anyway :)

Good place to chill with both your friends and families. A great place to take some pictures. Not recommended to come in the afternoon as the sun would shine you directly. Though, it is very nice when the weather is perfect. If you wish to take some good pictures, this place is really recommended. 

FYI the price is affordable.

Despite all the comments from negative critics, I would very much give this spot an A- since the maintenance has been taken into account very seriously. Considering this is a very big garden combined with lake and sea, I know it's hard to manage all the stuffs going on. But my recommendations is, can you reduce the strange smell that welcome us from the Tzu Chi gate? That's really disturbing...
Nice place for hang out, talks, meeting. Cool view. Yummy food, but some beverage just taste too sweet.

Loved the view and the place.
Best place to spend time with your special one, which ocean breeze blowing and some awesome milkshakes available, you can easily spend 1-2 hours of quality time.
Ordered Vanilla milkshake, Orange Juice and Lemon Squash which were awesome.
Very nice,  romantic place..love it...food n view are very nice❣
Nice ambience. Zuppa soupnya the best.
It brought a romantic atmosphere when the sun goes down. Sand area good enough to bring your kids. Beach not so clean, as peoples keep throwing garbage anywhere.
Nice and tasty food. Too many menu choices, the other Zenbus, don't have as much as menu as in PIK Avenue. Space a bit too crowded. Friendly staff.

A relaxing place that makes you feel like a holiday. A good place to makes you feel like you are not in Jakarta city. A cafe by the beach front, where you can take a sip of the coconut and ice tea while watching the sunsets accompanied by relaxing music background. I have come to this place many times, sometimes also for birthday parties or corporate events. Super relaxing.

The location is very nice, with secluded beach, clean and with professional staffs. We had prawns, crabs, pastas, and some appetizers, all delicious, albeit needed a bit more salt. The beer and wine selection is also OK, we sampled both red and white wines which were very good. It's a recommended place to have a night out at the beach in Jakarta.
Nice place facing the sea we like the food very much, much better than the other resto we had dinner before. Thanks for all delicious food n service.😋👍👍

Segarra used to be a hip and happening place back in the days around when they were opened. I was very impressed with everything they had to offer.

Now it seems like a totally different place...poorly maintained & rather run-down. It’s such a pity...Perhaps the only reason people still visit is to see the sunsets by the beach..however, with a minimal outdoor charge of 500K, it’s not a place that I want to frequent.

The menus are exuberantly expensive, quite more so than some 5-star hotels. Taste-wise...not bad, but not nearly as wow as the prices. Food-presentation-wise definitely don’t match. 

The only thing that saved me from writing a different sounding review was the impressively magestic sunset today and the friendly & helpful staff.

Best beachfront lounge and restaurant. The view are amazingly beautiful and romantic and the food can fill up your stomach with pleasure. 
I love all the dessert in this place. My favourite main dish are Grilled Honey Chicken Mustard and the Spaghetti.
You can enjoy regular beer up to the most exquisite winery here.
Love the view, the ambiance, the food and the service. 
I highly recommend it.
You can found best maccaroon recipe here
Good, little bit expensive
The red velvet cake is especially luscious. Price is a bit above other cake shop in area.
Macaroonnya banyak varian dan enak2 semu, tapi selain macaroon gabegitu rekomen sih produk lainnya
ini macaroons nya skarang keras banget ya kayak batu, biasanya enak dan empuk. kalo uda ga fresh jangan di jual dong.

I fell in love with the mural explaining about-something which I call- sustainable financial investment (borrowing from Brian Bolton's book title) in large pictures, on the wall of their cafe. I remember I took a video of it, but I don't know why I couldn't find it in my hard drive. Oh, ya, there was an exhibition when I visited Erasmus Huis. Check the photos out, the unique products they displayed. Love it.

Good place for chilling and for grab lunch while visit library. Good thing is their open for public, so without any appointment they'll open for you.  But the security guards are very strict. Good to know that
The place is neat and eye pleasing. You can have a meeting for scholarship consultancy here as well. They regularly have cultural events here for people to see and it's mostly if not all free!
Wonderfull place for interior and services. Parking lot should be available for public,but having the same location with the embassy may cause concern
Nice place to visit on strategic areas. Unfortunately the venue set has no seat available, at least when i visited it last time.

If you're an art lover and also a nationalist, this is the perfect place for you to visit. A museum dedicated to the arts of Basoeki Abdullah and all aspects of his life as an artist and as a nationalist. They also published many books and held many events and art exhibitions. Great service from the guides lead you to learn the history and greatness one of the Indonesian national treasure. A very cultured spot in the crowded Jakarta.

Actually love it, but not so many collection for painting, but you can see other collections such as masks, wayang, even weapons. Not large enough to spend for many hours, at least for me. I spend only around 40 minutes to get the tour complete. I like to enjoy the painting but bringing your kids not a very good combination. :)
Nice place to spend your weekend, this museum shows some paintings from maestro alm Basoeki Abdullah, and also some private stuff found on the day he passed away.
actually this museum is Basoeki Abdullah's house. it's a small museum that tells us about his career as a famous Indonesian painter. this museum also used to hold workshop.

Expect to be discriminated against if you are a foreigner at the front door, you will be charged five times more  then the locals for entry. 

Mr Basoeki Abdullah was a bigot according to he's work, look at his work and see how he portrays the Muslim versus how he portrays anyone else.

In the two big paintings he has of Muslims amongst many others he portrays the Muslim as horse riding War maniacs, he couldn't be further from the truth. 

Please someone tell me different.
Nice pools for lapping (50 meter Olympic pool), kids pools, slides, even static surfing. Admissions are pretty steep, especially during weekends and holidays.

Olympic size swimming pool (50mx20 m) with waterpark and flowraider machine
Clean restroom with warm water. 
Nice place to swim after work since it is not too crowded.  They have several ticketing promo (special hour ticket, group ticket, etc), so better to check into their website before you go there.

Don't forget that currently there are some locker fee (20k/2 coin). In the past, those lockers were free.

At first glance, this place looks like another water recreation place. You have an array of pools, like the kids fountain pool, wave pool, surf pool (you got to pay another 35 thousand rupiah), regular swimming pool, and slides with different level of heights.

Yet, the nice thing you have in this place is that it's not crowdy. Some people may love a crowdy place, but to me, it's the chance to explore different kind of pools without the possibility of stumble or got stomp by other swimmer. Every two hours, the wave pool activated for 30 minutes, so we got the chance to play with the wave and use our floater to swim through. It also got sliders with different speed so it's fun to go through it again, and again.

If you just want to spend the day swim and practicing your cardio, the regular swimming pool is the spot for you. With the olympic size and only 1.5 metres in depth, just enjoy your day swim your way.

At the end of the day, we can clean ourself in a heated shower, change our clothes (you can keep your belonging in the locker) and you're good to go.
Great location, next to the shopping mall. Many lifeguards ready in each pool. Recommended for a family with kids.
The water is quite clear. The olympic pool is good to learn because it is not too deep.
The lake in the middle of a big city is truly unique. Easy access and lots of sellers around the area so there's no need to worry.
Nice place, great view easy to get there. Closes at 5.
It used to be a nice and beautiful lake, but now.... hmmm...
Shaddy, nice but street seller stand should be attractive and should clean in area
It will be better if they can manage the area, traffic and most important is cleanliness
The food is Delicious.....and a nice place to hangout.
Nice place to eat right
Dajajl
I absolutely love their massamun curry! Their pad thai is okay, but I definitely recommend their curries more! Quick service and nice staff.

I always get spice level 3 and it’s fantastically awesome. I go there at least once a week. I love panang curry 😍😍😍
I recently tried spice level 6 (I was literally scared about thinking how it will turn out, but it wasn’t that hot 🤕)
Update- I don’t know who was the cook but this time spice level 6 was on par 😉🤩
I recommend the Pad Key Mao. It has a smooth spiciness about it which pairs with a nice sweetness.
It was awesome. Good was excellent Thank you to the whole restaurant staff. Also decent prices! You can't  beat it. 5 Plus!
Food was good. Price is good. Place is great. The server was not too patient.

The food here was tasty and the portion was big. I can easily say they don't sting on their beef slices because there were so many inside. The noodle was really yummy but it's own and we didn't need to add any chill or mint leaf. The soup had the just nice flavour for you to want to finish it all up. Only thing I didn't fancy was me and my friends had to wait almost 45 minutes to get a place. Besides that I'll surely come again to this place when visiting Vietnam

I enjoyed my lunch here.  Food was delicious.  Casual atmosphere.  Very busy when we visited, but fast service and tasty food in large portions for affordable prices.  Pho 2000 was recommended to us, and we were not disappointed.

The restaurant was famous for having President Clinton eat there. Not a big deal to me ;-)

The Pho was good, nothing special. I had better in Canada, much better in fact. The shrimp roll was a little better. I think this place has passed it prime.

Pho is ok here to compare with other Pho that i have been to before. Chicken rice , curry are good here. The restaurant is sometimes very crowded because guides recommend this place. 

This is where US president Bill Clinton came here in 2000 and he had Pho here with his daughter.
Good enough. Big portions. 6000vnd added to our bill in hand writing, apparently for napkins?! We didn't pay it and put the napkins back. Coffee downstairs is good though.
Good taste of coffee.simple service,affordable price.

Sate ayam, brenebon, cakalang, bakwan jagung tastes good. 
Serving time is very looong, so come before too hungry.
Have chess and another board game to play while waiting.

Nice and inexpensive. For those who likes Manadonese cuisine,inexpensive and halal, this is the place to go. For me, it's a shame it's halal coz no sate manado (pork), which is my favorite Manado food.
Kinds home cooked manado food. Best Woku dishes in Tangerang Area. See the menu below.... Recommend Bobara fillet or Marlin for Woku!

Expensive and unfriendly staff (cuek)...no tissue, spoon nor fork provided, so I have to call the waiter to bring one. Tissue came not in a box but only 2 pcs 😆.
And...google map mislead me to this place 😂😂😂

Marco serves traditional regional cuisine of Padang with a twist of peranakan style. The Pacific Place branch has a beautiful interior resembling old ambience. The cuisines can be good or not so good depending on your luck. When they first opened this branch, everything was perfect. However it degrades with time. What a pity! I love their chicken dishes, especially the rendang and pop ones, if they are prepared properly. They are delicious. But sometimes the meat was dry and the rice is not warm, which leave a deep disappointment to me.
Mindblown!! Premium Nasi Padang and actually worth the price. The coffee is just the right thing to have after a delicious meal. Thumbs up!!
This is extremely delicious..... I like also the beverage...lemon sereh , and martabak kelapa
Nice but pricey padang food
A padang restaurant serving Padangnese food and other Indonesian cuisine in a new level. I love the ice coffee.. give it a try.
Went there twice with Japanese colleagues; they knew exactly what to do, I would have been lost on my own.  The food was good, the service was good.
Nice choice of Japanese restaurants in Blok M in Jakarta.
Bye Sushi T*i.
ジャカルタの中のオアシス。おでんが美味しいです。お会計も安くて、とってもオススメ。
美味しい日本食食べるならここかな。お酒を多く呑む人は高くつくかも。
Its very peaceful and mind refreshing places, and mostly people are like to visit for catching SunSet 🌇 view.
It has the best view of lake with alot of greenry and margalla mountains and you can also get close to the water here.....love this place
Nice Place for At Evening time with friends or Family, and also u can enjoy BBQ,
Best place for camping and hiking. The sunset view is amazing
Such a good place for outing.

All pros, no cons!
-Atmosphere: Warm, inviting and cozy. You can sit on cushions on the floor or at tables, or in a very nice outdoor patio.
-Service is always very fast and polite.
-Free bread, soup and tea. The soup is some of the best lentil soup I've ever had!
-Food is delicious, always cooked perfectly, ample portions with generous sides.
-Very clearly marked vegan and vegetarian options, and lots of them, all very hearty and delicious! This is one of the best restaurants in Bloomington for vegans.
-10% discount for paying in cash

The food was extremely underwhelming and I dunno where they got “award winning bread” from. It tastes like leftovers that had just been heated up. The food wasn’t bad, I just expected a ton better because of the great reviews so my expectations may have been overinflated. The place is cute, the coffee was nice, and the amount of food was insane. Lots of quantity, not much quality.

Today was my first visit to Anatolia and aside from knowing that it was Turkish food and that they had a lunch buffet I really had no idea what to expect. When I walked in the lunch buffet was served partially in a bunch of hotel pans and partially in some bowls on another table like a family picnic. Now don't let that deter you as the food was decent, initially it just did not inspire a lot of confidence in my meal choice for the day. If I were to come here again, which inevitably I'm sure I will, I will probably order off the menu rather than having the buffet mainly due in part to the fact that most of the buffet options are vegetable dishes. If you are a vegetarian this would probably please you tremendously, however I am not. Everything said the food was good the staff was polite but a little overpriced.
This is a lovely restaurant and the food is really good! The prices are great and the service is excellent! I'd recommend to anyone.

Great olives and hummus. Their fresh bread is amazing. I found the rest of their food lacking anything special. I asked for a Sprite and was informed that they only carry diet Coke... Seriously. They do give free tea with every meal, though it smelled and tasted of old lawn clippings. I think I would have rather had the diet Coke. Lol

The place were good but im not into the food. I didn't mean its not good but not my kinda food I like. Came to here for live music. The singer so friendly and he also mingle to the customer and say thank you in the end of the night.
Seriously it has the best cuisine in town. The chicken wrap is undeniably delicious. Also, I tried their meat with bread (I dont know its name) and it's also great. I'm being honest.

A very good Shisha place in the southern part of Jakarta. Weekends have belly dance performance too. And yes, the shisha are good, with great options of snack and drinks too. A very cozy place to hangout with many people and stay for hours. Definitely recommended for all adults whether you're a Shisha lovers or not.
Cozy place to hangout. I tried apple fiz shisa. They said it is the lightest sisha for beginner

Nice place to have sisha..
Nice ambience
Nice food
Bale dance from 8- 11pm

Simple nice steak. Their cut is an approximate of their name at times, but still well worth it for the price. Surprisingly good side dishes such as the cream spinach and sauteed mushrooms. Very reasonable price.
Yummy steak, price worth it, nice ambience and friendly staffs.

Always love to eat in here.  The taste never failed my expectation.  And always craving for more

Our favorite menu in here is sirloin steak with terms of grilled medium,  so juicy and tender! 
Complete with spinach cooked so yummy that even if you dont like veggies,  you will love spinach in here
French fries is also our favorite,  but i try mashed potatoe today and also delicious and creamy
We can choose the steak sauce,  buddy's favorite / mushroom are both our favorite
For the drink,  nestea blackcurrent is alwasy fit for the meal

And the price is affordable with the joy after eating here
Especially if there's promo,  like today we try valentine promo called paket sayang. 
And it was so good,  we get sirloin Australia 200gr,  sirloin midfield 150gr, each of them complete with potatoes and veggies.  Then 2 glass of nestea,  and 2 glass of ice cream only for 175k rupiah (after tax) 
except small thing they cant serve the ice cream because the ice cream not available yet when we eat there at 11am

There are 2 floors available,  for smoking area outside on second floor. 
Always quite full in lunch and dinner in here

Parking lot is so small,  so they provide vallet parking service

The steak is good but the holy burger is so so. They still have promo free steak for customer who celebrate their birthday there. You should wear they birthday crown, its fun. The location is easy to find. The staff is friendly. One thing that you need to improve is the cleanliness of the toilet.
The food was delish and the ambience was quite cozy...

I'm originally from Chicago and relocated to Burlington to study at one of the local colleges. Upon my first semester in school, Red Square welcomed me to be a resident DJ at their venue - which later turned into two residencies per week. Red Square has always been there for me and helped me advance in my DJ passion and my efforts to be a professional marketer.

The Red Square environment is fun and exciting! As a DJ, I always see our guests enjoying themselves and having a memorable time. There are multiple stages in the venue that DJs and live bands perform on throughout the week. That being said, Red Square is the place to be for an array of music.
Great drinks & staff.  Always a good time!  Nothing better then a summer night having drinks on their patio and listening to music!!

I'm giving this 3 stars as bring a bit of an older couple it seemed more of a dive bar. they had live music which was fun, a lounge area and a dance and DJ area in the back. it seemed a little different than what we are used to and being a big beer drinker we stopped in for a drink. My fiance said the shock top didnt taste like normal and my ipa left a dry aftertaste in my mouth. so I'm not sure if I'd be returning. it was clean inside and friendly staff just not sure if it's a place for me.

WAY BIGGER THAN IT LOOKS! Step inside to a small dining like area and step up to the dance floor. A DJ room in the back corner and live music outside in the summer time. Only downside is the bathroom situation, (especially for gents apparently) but other than that, an awesome place to hang with friends.

What fun night life! We were in the area for a wedding and stopped in for late night drinks. The band you had was very entertaining and we ended up staying for a couple hours. Dancing, drinking, socializing...Thanks for the experience

It was hot. There were many stairs. I could not figure the path to see the exhibits. I kept running into do not enter signs. 
Almost all signs are in Indonesian. 
There was a band playing very loud music with distorted speakers in courtyard. 
I only stayed about 30 minutes.

It's huge place to visit, nice miniature, the Information it's really impressive.. but kinda hot inside ... Overall it's pretty nice museum to visit.. and to go there it's not hard, besides we can get free bus ride to go another place

Good place to visit with family and friends. Those who like to have photo hunting for old historical building and location. So many beautiful spot and museums near by the building m

You can also having culinary and family picnic, there are bicycles rental too.

As I step in  to the square plaza of Kota Tua, the building if this museum is the first thing I see. Really amazing. It makes me feel like I am somewhere else... not Jakarta. The collection of the museum is actually interesting, but the way they are  presented perhaps needs to be changed to be more exciting.

One of the best spot in Jakarta to feel the nuances of this old town under the governance of East-indie. The museum got some historical stuffs and cultural legacy around the development of Jakarta from VOC era. Not only the History Museum, the field outside it and the cafe around still maintain the feel of Batavia. You can sees the birds crowding the road, riding around with bicycle, go to the restaurants and cafes, buy some merchandise, visits a few museum just by walking, or even just to sit and relax along with the scenery.

A very calm and soothing place to enjoy a fine history of ceramics. 

Perfect for those who loves enjoying arts in a classic dutch design building.
Great museum... A lot of collection and my child can make ceramic by himself, the staffs are also helpful & warm, the air-conditioned in every room are quite good

Great place to visit in Jakarta, specifically in Kota Tua. The ticket price is cheap, the place and clean, and it has so many historical until contemporary painting. It also showed the tools to paint and some heritage stuffs
Entrance fee only Rp 5000 .its good museum with  that price. It's holiday education for ur kids too.

The Museum's collection is interesting enough for those who love arts. As we can learn that beautiful arts are in our blood since he very first time. Human are even more creative in past years and it left over an inheritance for history. The location is in Kota Tua Site. While i came here at the crowd of New Year holiday, this place is pampering us with peace and space. Aside of museum, the buildings has its own wonderful ambience. It is old. It is warm. And it has little green park with chair for the visitor to take a short rest while feel the air breeze. Suitable for family who bring children. We went back home happily with nice experience here, remembering that we passed another Museums were very crowded and uncomfortable for infant. Ticket only IDR 5000/person (children under 2 yrs no need to buy ticket)
A well-known noodle joint with delicious fried  dumplings. Now is having 50% offer using Dana apps. Must try the longevity noodles on promo.
Good service. Taste is not bad. But has many shortcomings. Price is quite expensive, portion is small. Also place is too bright and very close distance to other customers. ~ Not recommended ~

Bakmi GM at Puri is the branch of one of the oldest Noodle Restaurant at Jakarta. Years the taste is almost same. Unfortunately some branches use paper cup and plastic spoon and fork at the where all people in the world try to minimize the usage of plastic. We go to eat only to the big restaurant and not to their branches at malls.
Historical n legend noodle that we knew since '80 n now grew with modern n life style concep
The taste is good. Service ok, but the price is more expensive now

Affordable steak, taste really good considering the cheap price. No complains here. 

Serving was also pretty fast.

The place now os really cozy with a casual touch. Keep it up!
Superb steak with affordable price. Never fail. Must try!
Quick and friendly service. The coffee was good. The steaks were just ok for their price range. Good place to eat steak on a budget

If you want a good steak, with good steak, with cheap price this is the place for you. Though the chef sometimes just couldn't differentiate between a medium, medium well, and well done steak. On the plus side, You could order a steak and eat it with rice like a barbarian...hohoho

affordable and dependable steak. for under 100K you got 200gr of secondary cut wagyu. this outlet at gajah mada street is more comfortable compared to the one at pecenongan. the grilled chicken is also good
The food quality is very consistent...never failed when go here....it always have its unique charc flavour from the fire in the wok.....
The Best beef rice noodle.. but place need more clean up.. seriously..

Not too tasty.. Not much impression
Just normal beef kwe tiau
Classic chinese kwetiauw in town. The fried and siram was lovely and made this place a must visit when I'm visiting Mangga Besar
Authentic Beef Kwe Tiaw taste accompanied by old school chinese cuisine atmosphere.

This place really hits the spot, especially on a cool or rainy day. A dish that radiates with the vibrance of spring. Got a pretty good portion size for a relatively affordable price. Should definitely try this place out if you have time on your hands.
Big portion. You should try the fish soup
Good food, super delicious
Good chinese food especially Sop Ikan, Wongsan Cah Fumak, Kodok Mentega, Mie Goreng. The food prices are not cheap.
Great chinese food restaurant, clean, nice service, fresh food. My favorite is shrimp in here

Been there to Nanny's Pavillon Terrace Central Park, the places is quite comfy in the outside 'cause surrounded by the park itself also Koi pond, relaxing and calmfull.

For the menu's the Waffles and Pancakes its great and won for my hearts from Olivia's Sizzling Green Tea its so good and must order first, second is Bruce's Sausage Cheesy, Third is Janice's Meatball Brown Sauce Cheesy, and the last Emma's Hot Banana Cheesy, even tho this pancake just using honey, and banana its satisfy me! Yikes... but the services it took a little bit of time

After all, they have another menu's like salad, chicken, pasta and many more, you should come ;P
Nice ambience good food. I love the salad and fried mushrooms. The Green Chicken Sausage Pasta has a very nice pesto sauce. The desserts are great.

Serving good pasta and pancakes. Their french fries seasoned with melted cheese is definitely my personal favorite dish.
Decor is nice inside, but not so much at the outside. Instagrammable you might say.
Fast service here, althought some of the staff should try to smile more. :)

Food taste: very good
Place: cozy
Price: standard
One of the best pasta in town. If you haven't got any promos, creating a never-expired member card will guarantee you 10% discount every time. Nice ambience too.

Its a good place to eat
And thats a lot of food we can buy in There
The location is Central Park Mall

Bau kecoa dan ada tikus!
Baru tadi sore kami makan di sana. Bau kecoa sangat menusuk di tempat duduk tipe sofa yg memanjang di depan kwetiau sapi Pontianak 88. Tp krn beberapa teman sedang makan, saya menahan diri utk memberitahu mereka. 
Kalau mau makan, sebaiknya cari area depan/tengah yang kursinya satuan/tidak menyambung, dan bukan yang ada joknya spt sofa. Dan hindari area2 pojok. Lalu ada tikus di depan kios di sebelah kwetiauw tsb, mengagetkan pengunjung yg sedang makan. Dan dikejar oleh seorang anak kecil, tikus itu menghilang di sela2 kios.
Apa manajemen tidak pernah melakukan anti hama?! Saya yakin banyak kecoa di balik jok sofa tsb! Dan tikus muncul di tempatnya orang makan, itu sangat menjijikkan!!
foodcourt di central park dgn tempat duduk yg tdk terlalu banyak. buat rombongan keluarga agak kesulitan mencari tempat duduk di saat ramai.
Banyaaaak banget pilihan makanan disini. Tempatnya juga cukup luas 👌

I am reviewing the restaurant of the hotel, not the hotel itself and the accommodations. I have come here multiple times to eat lunch here. The hotel restaurant has a daily all-you-can-eat regime menu. The dishes served each day are rather diverse and the quality of the dishes is very high. That plus a nice staff, somewhat classy atmosphere and excellent price make this an easy choice for everyone in the area that wants to enjoy a good lunch.

I stayed at Hotel Capitol for almost 2 weeks. I was traveling for business. My guess is that the building was renovated not so long ago. It's quite clean though I found a paper clip on the floor of my room and it remained there for my entire stay - meaning nobody vacuumed there or wasn't really thorough. Also the toiled smelled a little sometimes, not always though (or maybe I got used to it). I was not a big fan of the breakfasts either. The bread was okay but not the freshest, the toast bread was dry and hard. Not much of a choice regarding what to put on that bread too. When you enter the restaurant to grab the breakfast there is no one standing by the door usually. Sooner or later one of the waiters would come up to you and ask you for your room number. Sometimes they looked displeased, sometimes scared and once I encountered a nervous lady who didn't understand the room number in English. I had to point the number on the page for her.
That being said I am quite happy with my stay. The room smelled sweet and nice every time I entered. I appreciate that during the weekend the cleaning lady saw me leaving for breakfast in the morning and cleaned my room before I came back. The reception staff was the nicest and very helpful (with one exception when I was told that nothing can be done about my request, later on I asked a different person and there was no issue with doing what I asked for). I would like to say extra thank you to Georgia, receptionist who was the sweetest to me.

No way this is a four star hotel. The rooms were to small for a couple, the food was average at best. Some of the staff were not pleasant.
Most disturbing was the shower - the water suddenly go very hot and than very cold by itself! We almost got a burn when we showered. Definitely won't be coming there again.
